This disc imprinted classic Bonham drum fills, blistering guitar riffs and inimitable vocals on a generation that came to believe that it could change the world. This record, with its songs stolen from unremembered bluesmen, may have had some effect, but the lasting impact may just be the perfect example of a whole being greater than the sum of its parts. It is emergence that drives and evolves and makes the world slightly altered one moment from the next, even if it is only possibilities...
